If you would like to help us extend our platforms and SDKs stack, you are more than welcome to contact us or contribute to the [Indobase SDK Generator](https://github.com/Indobase/sdk-generator) project GitHub repository and read our contribution guide.

# Protocols {% #protocols %}
We are always looking to add new SDKs to our platform. If the SDK you are looking for is still missing, labeled as beta or experimental, or you simply do not want to integrate with an SDK, you can always integrate with indobase directly using any standard HTTP, GraphQL, or WebSocket clients and the relevant indobase protocol.

indobase supports multiple API protocols for maximum flexibility and developer convenience. You can learn more about how to integrate directly with them using one of the following available guides:

{% cards %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/apis/realtime" title="Realtime API" %}
Integrate with the indobase Realtime API
{% /cards_item %}

{% cards_item href="/docs/apis/rest" title="REST API" %}
Integrate with the indobase REST API
{% /cards_item %}

{% cards_item href="/docs/apis/graphql" title="GraphQL API" %}
Integrate with the indobase GraphQL API
{% /cards_item %}
{% /cards %}

# Utility classes {% #utility-classes %}
indobase's SDKs provide useful utility classes to make your development experience easier.
Use these classes and methods to reduce guess work and get better code suggestions in your IDE.

## IDs {% #ids %}
indobase has utility classes to help you handle IDs. 
These generate the correct ID format to be passed to the indobase APIs.

{% tabs %}
{% tabsitem #client title="Client SDKs" %}
{% multicode %}
```client-web
import { Client, Account } from "Indobase";

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```client-flutter
import 'package:Indobase/Indobase.dart';

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom()
```
```client-apple
import Indobase

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```client-android-kotlin
import io.Indobase.ID

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
{% /multicode %}
{% /tabsitem %}

{% tabsitem #server title="Server SDKs" %}
{% multicode %}
```server-nodejs
const sdk = require('node-Indobase');

// Generate a unique ID
sdk.ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
sdk.ID.custom("my-custom-id")

```
```deno
import * as sdk from "npm:node-Indobase";
// Generate a unique ID
sdk.ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
sdk.ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```php
<?php

use indobase\ID;

// Generate a unique ID
ID::unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID::custom("my-custom-id")
```
```python
from Indobase.id import ID

# Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

# Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```csharp
using indobase.ID;

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```dart
import 'package:dart_Indobase/dart_Indobase.dart';

// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```java
io.Indobase.ID
// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```kotlin
io.Indobase.ID
// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```ruby
require 'Indobase'

include Indobase
ß
# Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

# Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
```swift
import Indobase
// Generate a unique ID
ID.unique()

// Generate a custom ID
ID.custom("my-custom-id")
```
{% /multicode %}
{% /tabsitem %}
{% /tabs %}

indobase generates unique IDs that are both **random** and **ordered**. 
indobase IDs combine a timestamp prefix based on microseconds and a random UID string, formatted as `<timestamp_hex><uid_hex>`.

## Enums {% #enums %}
indobase has enumeration classes for predefined strings used different parameters used for the indobase APIs.

These enums are available for authenticator type, name, OAuth provider, 
password hash types, browsers, authentication factors, index types, credit cards, 
image gravity, image format, relationship types, SMTP encryption, Function runtime, 
messaging provider type, compression algorithms, execution methods, and country flags.
{% tabs %}
{% tabsitem #client title="Client SDKs" %}
You can discover the available enums in each SDK at the source.

